  "body": "I'm running into an issue with React 0.14 with regards to [exposing component functions](https://facebook.github.io/react/tips/expose-component-functions.html).  Perhaps I am just doing something wrong, unless this is a stale piece of documentation from an earlier version of React.\n\nI have a React component that exposes a piece of state as a function, e.g.:\n\n``` coffeescript\nSelectionsController = React.createClass\n  propTypes:\n    values: array\n\n  getInitialState: ->\n    selections: []\n\n  getSelections: ->\n    @state.selections\n\n  render: ->\n    `<ul>{this.props.values.map(this.renderValue)}</ul>`\n\n  renderValue: (value) ->\n    `<li><Checkbox name={value}\n                   checked={_.contains(this.state.selections, value)}\n                   onChange={this.handleChangeCurry(value)} /></li>`\n\n  handleChangeCurry: (value) ->\n    (checked) =>\n      if checked\n        @setState(selections: _.union(@state.selections, [value]))\n      else\n        @setState(selections: _.without(@state.selections, value))\n```\n\nI then create an instance of this component and later try to fetch the selections via `getSelections`:\n\n``` coffeescript\ncontroller = React.createElement(SelectionsController, values: ['one', 'two', 'three'])\n# then in a user event handler...\nconsole.log(controller.getSelections())\n```\n\nThe console log line results in this error:\n\n> Uncaught TypeError: controller.getSelections is not a function\n\nAm I doing something wrong?\n",
